In this update:
[1] Gaya, Bihar state
[2] Uttar Pradesh state
[3] Kheri district, Uttar Pradesh state

******
[1] Gaya, Bihar state
Date: Thu 1 Sep 2016 10.46 AM IST
Source: The Times of India (TOI), Times News Network (TNN) [edited]
http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/patna/Three-more-suspected-AES-cases-reported-in-Gaya/articleshow/53968415.cms


Even as health officials struggle to contain the acute encephalitis syndrome (AES) menace through immunisation, early hospitalisation and awareness campaigns, 3 more patients were admitted to the Anugrah Narayan Magadh Medical College Hospital (ANMMCH) [in Gaya, Bihar] during the last couple of days.

With this, the number of AES patients admitted to ANMMCH this season has gone up to 82. While 2 AES patients were admitted on [Tue 30 Aug 2016], one more patient was admitted on [Wed 31 Aug 2016].

AES patients are undergoing treatment in the children's ward of the hospital. Hospital superintendent Dr SK Sinha also confirmed that 3 new AES patients have been admitted to the hospital. The patients have undergone tests for Japanese encephalitis.

At this stage, hospital staff are not in a position to say whether the patients admitted are suffering from Japanese encephalitis or some other disease.

Altogether, 32 of the AES patients died in the hospital while another 9 are undergoing treatment, Dr Sinha said. While 40 patients were either discharged or were lured by touts operating in the hospital vicinity promising better treatment in private nursing homes. The mortality rate of the AES patients in Gaya is said to be on the higher side of the acceptable limit. It is well ahead of the average, feel experts.

Asked about the facilities available in the ANMMCH for rehabilitation of AES survivors, hospital superintendent SK Sinha said several facilities including trained physiotherapists are available in the hospital but the survivors rarely avail them. Once discharged, the survivors, despite counselling of the attendants do not come back for follow-up check up, said Dr Sinha.

[byline: Abdul Qadir]

