******
[2] Uttar Pradesh state
Date: Sun 28 Aug 2016
Source: Web India 123 [edited]
http://news.webindia123.com/news/Articles/India/20160828/2926226.html


After 3 more deaths of children due to encephalitis in Baba Raghav Das Medical College Hospital [in Gorakhpur, Uttar Pradesh] during the past 24 hours now death toll mounted to 188 today [28 Aug 2016]. Official sources here said among the 3 deceased, one was from Gorakhpur, one from Maharaj Nagar and one from Bihar. Sources said 729 patients of the disease have been admitted Baba Raghav Das Medical College Hospital since [1 Jan 2016]. Recently, 16 new patients of encephalitis had been admitted, while total 94 patients suffering from this disease were getting treatment in the hospital. Patients of encephalitis from Gorakhpur, Basti, Azamgarh, Ballia, Gonda, Mau, Gazipur, Balrampur, Ambedkar Nagar, Badaun districts and from nearby states like Bihar and Jharkhand also from neighboring country Nepal are getting treatment in Medical college hospital of Gorakhpur.

